J-K: Two militants escape after exchanging gunfire with security forces in Pulwama 
17-3-2017 
An encounter broke out between security forces and militants in Batnoor, Lassipora area of Pulwama district in Jammu and Kashmir on Friday morning.

The area has been cordoned off by defence personnel, but two militants who were trapped fled from the spot.

Earlier this week, three militants were killed in encounter at Kupwara that took place in Kalaroos area of Kashmir.

More details awaited. 
